properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 13 at 5:59PM CST until January 14 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Hastings NE
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibility one quarter mile or less in dense fog.

* WHERE...Portions of north central Kansas and central, east
central and south central Nebraska, all counties east of the
Highway 281 corridor.

* WHEN...Until 3 AM CST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility. In
addition, sub-freezing surface temperatures may combine with fog
to cause slick spots, especially on bridges and overpasses.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Visibility will vary somewhat tonight, and
dense fog will probably not occur the entire time the Advisory
is in effect. As drier air moves in from the west, dense fog
will likely improve first in Nebraska counties north of Highway
6, and perhaps linger the longest in southern counties such as
Thayer, Jewell and Mitchell.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM CST TUESDAY
